# Privacy Policy

Effective Date: May 25, 2026

Welcome to Postmarked ("Postmarked," "we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you use the Postmarked website and related services.

Postmarked is a private travel-sharing platform that allows users to share travel updates, photos, locations, and trip posts with friends, family, and subscribers.

## Information We Collect

We may collect the following information:

- Account information such as name, email address, username, and profile details
- User-generated content including posts, photos, captions, comments, and location information
- Device and browser information
- Log data such as IP address, timestamps, and usage activity
- Communication preferences and notification settings

## How We Use Information

We use collected information to:

- Provide and operate the Postmarked service
- Deliver travel updates and notifications requested by users
- Improve the functionality, reliability, and security of the platform
- Respond to support requests and user inquiries
- Prevent abuse, spam, fraud, or unauthorized access

## Sharing of Information

We do not sell personal information.

We may share limited information with third-party service providers that help operate the service, including hosting providers, analytics providers, and authentication providers.

Information may also be disclosed if required by law or to protect the security and integrity of the service.

## Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect user information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely secure.

## User Content

Users are responsible for the content they upload and share through Postmarked. Users should only share content they have the right to distribute.

## Third-Party Links

Postmarked may contain links to third-party websites or services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of third-party sites.

## Children's Privacy

Postmarked is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information. If you believe a child under 13 has provided personal information, please contact the site administrator.

## Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Continued use of the service after changes become effective constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
